text: Acestrorhynchus lacustris is a species of fish in the family Acestrorhynchidae. It was described by Christian Frederik Lütken in 1875, originally under the genus Xiphorhamphus. It inhabits the São Francisco and Paraná River. It reaches a maximum standard length of . A. lacustris spawns between July–March.Spawning for Acestrorhynchus lacustris at www.fishbase.org. ==References== Category:Acestrorhynchidae Category:Fish described in 1875
